# Flashy Cardy Course - Project Structure

This is a Next.js 15 flashcard application built with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and the App Router.

## Project Architecture

- **App Router**: This project uses Next.js App Router (not Pages Router)
- **Source Directory**: All application code is in the `src/` directory
- **Import Alias**: Use `@/` to import from the `src/` directory (configured in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json))

## Directory Structure

- `src/app/` - Application routes and layouts using App Router
  - [layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - Root layout with metadata and fonts
  - [page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - Home page component
  - [globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) - Global styles and Tailwind directives
- `src/components/` - Reusable React components
  - `ui/` - shadcn/ui components (installed via CLI)
  - Custom application components (create as needed)
- `src/lib/` - Utility functions and helpers
  - [utils.ts](mdc:src/lib/utils.ts) - cn() utility for class merging
- `public/` - Static assets like images and fonts

## Key Configuration Files

- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind CSS configuration with shadcn/ui theme
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration with path aliases
- [components.json](mdc:components.json) - shadcn/ui configuration
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts

## Development Scripts

- `npm run dev` - Start development server
- `npm run build` - Build for production
- `npm run start` - Start production server
- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint
